definition.value: A pentanone carrying an oxo substituent at position 2.
A steroid sulfate obtained by the formal condensation of hydroxy group at position 21 of cortisol with sulfuric acid.
The reduced form of NADP+; used in anabolic reactions, such as lipid and nucleic acid synthesis, which require NADPH as a reducing agent.
An ammonium ion that is a derivative of L-histidine having a 3-carboxy-3-(methylammonio)propyl group at the 2-position on the imidazole ring.
